      <details>
        <summary>How many bags of concrete are in a cubic yard?</summary>
        <p>For standard 80-pound bags of pre-mixed concrete, you need approximately 45 bags to make one cubic yard. For 60-pound bags, you need about 60 bags per cubic yard, and for 40-pound bags, about 90 bags. Each 80-pound bag yields roughly 0.6 cubic feet of mixed concrete, and there are 27 cubic feet in a cubic yard (27 / 0.6 = 45). For projects requiring more than about 1 cubic yard, ordering ready-mix delivery is usually cheaper and much faster than mixing bags by hand.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How much does a cubic yard of concrete weigh?</summary>
